
[1]firmness

   FIRM'NESS, n. ferm'ness.

   1. Closeness or denseness of texture or structure; compactness;
   hardness; solidity; as the firmness of wood, stone, cloth or other
   substance.

   2. Stability; strength; as the firmness of a union, or of a
   confederacy.

   3. Steadfastness; constancy; fixedness; as the firmness of a purpose or
   resolution; the firmness of a man, or of his courage; firmness of mind
   or soul.

   4. Certainty; soundness; as the firmness of notions or opinions.
